content.text:
The issue was that the prepublish screen (modal) was showing the "Categories" option even for Pages, where it shouldn't be applicable. This occurred because the "Categories" item was being added to the UI state list unconditionally in `PrepublishingHomeViewModel.kt`.

I have fixed this by moving the logic for adding the "Categories" item into the `showNotSetPost` function. The `showNotSetPost` function is already guarded by a check `if (!editPostRepository.isPage)`, ensuring that it (and now the "Categories" item) is only executed for Posts, not Pages.

This change ensures that:
1.  **Pages** will no longer show the "Categories" option in the prepublish modal.
2.  **Posts** will continue to show the "Categories" option (along with Tags) as before.

The file `WordPress/src/main/java/org/wordpress/android/ui/posts/prepublishing/home/PrepublishingHomeViewModel.kt` was modified to implement this logic.

1.  Removed the unconditional addition of the Categories item in `setupHomeUiState`.
2.  Updated `showNotSetPost` to include the Categories item, preserving the existing behavior for Posts while excluding it for Pages.

No other files needed modification.

```kotlin
// In setupHomeUiState
if (!editPostRepository.isPage) {
    showNotSetPost(editPostRepository, site)
}

// In showNotSetPost
// ... (Tags logic)
val categoriesString = getCategoriesUseCase.getPostCategoriesString(editPostRepository, site)
add(HomeUiState(
    navigationAction = PrepublishingScreenNavigation.Categories,
    // ...
))
```

